Neel Krishnaswami wrote:
> 
>   module type FOO =
>     sig
>       type t
>       val v : t
>     end
>   
>   module type BAR = (* This is a subtype of FOO *)
>     sig
>       type t
>       val v : t
>       val v' : t
>     end
> 
> Notice that there's no syntax to abbreviate the definition of BAR;

Sure there is:

    module type BAR =
      sig
        include FOO
        val v' : t
      end

should work like a charm. ;-)

